Acer, Hon Hai Precision Industry, TSMC: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-05-11T00:38:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/acer-hon-hai-precision-industry-tsmc-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Taiex Index fell 12.20, or 0.1 percent, to 9,023.28.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT): J.T. Wang, chairman of the world’s
second-largest supplier of laptops, said he’s close to deciding
to buy a  software developer  and the company has narrowed the
search to one to two overseas candidates. Acer is seeking a
software developer that would help make personal computers,
smartphones and tablets more compatible with each other, he
said, declining to provide details such as names or how much
Acer prepared to spend.  Separately, the company’s April sales fell 23 percent to
NT$28 billion from a year earlier, according to a statement
filed to the Taiwan Stock Exchange. The stock dropped 1.1
percent to NT$53.60.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317 TT): The world’s
largest contract maker of electronics said April sales rose 33
percent to NT$205 billion from a year earlier, according to a
statement filed to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange . The stock was
unchanged at NT$109.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330 TT): The
world’s largest custom maker of chips said April sales rose 11
percent to NT$36 billion from a year earlier, according to a
statement filed to the Taiwan Stock Exchange. The stock dropped
1.5 percent to NT$74.40.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
